<section class="install" id="install" aria-labelledby="install-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section-header">
      <p class="section-eyebrow">// 01 — Install</p>
      <h2 id="install-heading" class="section-title">One command bootstraps everything.</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">The curl line installs <code>clarity</code> — the manager that builds, installs, and switches icon themes for you. After that, every Clarity variant and every community theme is one command away.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="install-grid">
      <div>
        <ol class="install-steps">
          <li class="install-step">
            <span class="install-step-num">01</span>
            <div><strong>Install the manager</strong><span>One <code>curl | bash</code> drops the <code>clarity</code> binary into <code>~/.local/bin</code>. Works on any GTK-based desktop — GNOME, Cinnamon, MATE, XFCE, Budgie, elementary.</span></div>
          </li>
          <li class="install-step">
            <span class="install-step-num">02</span>
            <div><strong>Install a theme</strong><span><code>clarity install @user/theme</code> fetches and builds any community theme into <code>~/.local/share/icons</code>. The nine core Clarity variants come pre-installed.</span></div>
          </li>
          <li class="install-step">
            <span class="install-step-num">03</span>
            <div><strong>Switch with one word</strong><span><code>clarity use &lt;theme&gt;</code> activates a theme and refreshes the icon cache. No logout, no settings panel.</span></div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <figure class="terminal" aria-label="Install command in a terminal window">
        <div class="terminal-bar">
          <span class="terminal-dots" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span>
          <span class="terminal-title">kuba@desktop: ~</span>
          <button class="terminal-copy" type="button" data-copy-target="#install-cmd" aria-label="Copy install command to clipboard">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#i-copy"/></svg>
            <span class="terminal-copy-label">Copy</span>
          </button>
        </div>
<pre class="terminal-body" aria-label="Shell session">
<span class="term-comment"># 1. Bootstrap the clarity manager</span>
<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cmd" id="install-cmd">curl -sL https://clarity.pl.eu.org/install | bash</span>

<span class="term-comment"># 2. Switch to a built-in variant</span>
<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cmd">clarity use caeruleus</span>

<span class="term-comment"># 3. Or grab a community theme by @user/name</span>
<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cmd">clarity install @jcubic/cyberpunk</span>

<span class="term-prompt">$</span> <span class="term-cursor" aria-hidden="true"></span>
</pre>

      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
